1
00:00:13,867 --> 00:00:16,033
<i>That's why that jerk doesn't
answer the phone anymore.</i>

2
00:00:16,167 --> 00:00:17,033
<i> Grandmother...</i>

3
00:00:17,167 --> 00:00:17,967
<i> Sir Tonyo, thank you.</i>

4
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:19,100
<i> It's Lee and Bal,</i>

5
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:22,067
<i>they're the ones
who found your grandmother.</i>

6
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:23,367
<i> What did I do wrong to you?</i>

7
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:24,833
<i> Stay away from Faye Guerrero.</i>

8
00:00:24,967 --> 00:00:25,833
<i> You know what?</i>

9
00:00:25,967 --> 00:00:28,133
<i>Some men jumped on Vince
on his way home.</i>

10
00:00:28,267 --> 00:00:31,200
<i>I'm just protecting my sister
like I protect you.</i>

11
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:33,000
<i> We don't need your protection.</i>

12
00:00:33,133 --> 00:00:35,567
<i>I'm a grown woman
and so is your sister.</i>

13
00:00:35,733 --> 00:00:37,567
<i>Can't you just let us
live our lives?</i>

14
00:00:37,700 --> 00:00:38,933
<i> Dante was warned, Sir.</i>

15
00:00:39,067 --> 00:00:40,767
<i> He knew he was being watched.</i>

16
00:00:40,900 --> 00:00:42,300
<i>He even knew the vehicle
we were in,</i>

17
00:00:42,433 --> 00:00:43,467
<i> so he shot at us immediately.</i>

18
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:45,633
<i> We need to plan this properly.</i>

19
00:00:45,767 --> 00:00:48,267
<i>But I want to assume that
everyone is compromised.</i>

20
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:49,633
<i> This is your job now.</i>

21
00:00:49,767 --> 00:00:53,200
<i>Make sure that Dante's name
doesn't get attached to boss.</i>

22
00:00:53,333 --> 00:00:55,500
<i>What did you have
for breakfast this morning?</i>

23
00:00:55,633 --> 00:00:56,700
<i> I can't remember.</i>

24
00:00:56,833 --> 00:00:58,000
<i> Bobby, let's go home.</i>

25
00:00:58,133 --> 00:00:59,533
<i> I'm not sick.</i>

26
00:00:59,667 --> 00:01:02,233
<i>Sorry for my questions, Mother.</i>

27
00:01:02,367 --> 00:01:05,767
<i>Just a moment,
I'll talk to your granddaughter.</i>

28
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:07,767
<i>It's possible
that she has dementia.</i>

29
00:01:07,933 --> 00:01:09,033
<i> Dementia?</i>

30
00:01:09,167 --> 00:01:11,400
<i>Isn't there no cure
for dementia?</i>

31
00:01:11,533 --> 00:01:15,033
<i>There are treatments to manage
the symptoms, but you're right.</i>

32
00:01:15,167 --> 00:01:18,300
<i>There's no known cure
for dementia so far.</i>

33
00:01:43,700 --> 00:01:44,667
Hello, Tonyo?

34
00:01:46,667 --> 00:01:48,233
Hello, Bobby?

35
00:01:50,067 --> 00:01:51,767
How's Grandmother Isang?

36
00:01:55,633 --> 00:01:58,367
Tonyo, grandmother is sick.

37
00:01:58,500 --> 00:02:02,233
Most likely, dementia.

38
00:02:10,533 --> 00:02:13,100
What does Grandmother Isang
need, Bobby?

39
00:02:13,233 --> 00:02:15,300
Right now, nothing.

40
00:02:15,467 --> 00:02:20,833
But she needs to go through
tests to confirm

41
00:02:20,967 --> 00:02:24,467
if she really
has a dimentia.

42
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:29,333
And you, do you need anything?

43
00:02:29,467 --> 00:02:31,733
Just tell me, okay?

44
00:02:31,867 --> 00:02:34,667
Tonyo...

45
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:37,967
I've been absent for two days.

46
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:40,900
I wasn't able to get permission
from the Chief.

47
00:02:41,033 --> 00:02:42,600
I'll take care of that.

48
00:02:42,733 --> 00:02:44,133
Thank you.

49
00:02:44,267 --> 00:02:46,867
Besides, I need to
file for leave.

50
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,400
Bobby...

51
00:02:49,567 --> 00:02:52,000
Don't think about it anymore.

52
00:02:52,133 --> 00:02:54,500
What's important is
Grandmother Isang.

53
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:57,133
Thank you.

54
00:02:57,267 --> 00:03:01,233
I just have something
to take care of, but...

55
00:03:01,367 --> 00:03:03,567
I'll visit you right away.

56
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:05,333
Thank you.

57
00:03:05,467 --> 00:03:07,200
Okay.

58
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:00,867
Good morning, Mayor.

59
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,333
Hello.

60
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:09,633
Cecilia isn't answering me.

61
00:04:09,767 --> 00:04:12,833
Glen, if he doesn't want
to pay attention to you,

62
00:04:12,967 --> 00:04:15,800
it means he doesn't want
to talk to you.

63
00:04:15,933 --> 00:04:18,300
It's that simple.

64
00:04:18,433 --> 00:04:18,933
Okay.

65
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:21,567
Oh...

66
00:04:23,133 --> 00:04:26,633
If she doesn't want to talk to
me, why did someone text me?

67
00:04:29,367 --> 00:04:30,967
<i> Dante is gone.</i>

68
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:32,533
<i>Robles is making sure no one
will get in trouble.</i>

69
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:37,000
What did Cecilia say?

70
00:04:39,833 --> 00:04:41,733
It's not her.

71
00:04:41,867 --> 00:04:44,467
See? She doesn't want
to talk to you.

72
00:04:49,067 --> 00:04:53,600
Bok, it looks like Enriquez
really didn't come today.

73
00:04:53,733 --> 00:04:54,600
I told you.

74
00:04:54,733 --> 00:04:56,933
You should have talked
to her last night.

75
00:04:57,067 --> 00:05:00,800
Oh, why are you
blaming me again?

76
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:03,167
Why? Who else?

77
00:05:03,300 --> 00:05:05,167
Well, actually,

78
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:06,400
this could be my fault again

79
00:05:06,533 --> 00:05:08,900
because I didn't
conduct a workshop

80
00:05:09,033 --> 00:05:12,333
when it comes
to handling love life.

81
00:05:12,467 --> 00:05:13,900
Don't worry, Bok...

82
00:05:14,033 --> 00:05:17,533
when I have extra time,
I'll train you.

83
00:05:17,667 --> 00:05:19,900
I'll give you a seminar.

84
00:05:20,033 --> 00:05:22,000
- Sir.
- Sir.

85
00:05:22,133 --> 00:05:23,500
All right.

86
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:28,133
Men...

87
00:05:28,267 --> 00:05:30,600
We need to focus.

88
00:05:30,733 --> 00:05:33,333
We have an important
mission today.

89
00:05:33,467 --> 00:05:37,433
Yesterday, Garcia and Conde...

90
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:39,333
killed the one who let Mando
escape.

91
00:05:39,467 --> 00:05:42,933
Unfortunately, we haven't gotten
any information...

92
00:05:43,067 --> 00:05:47,900
that can point
to who ordered him.

93
00:05:48,033 --> 00:05:51,500
Sir, I already spoke
to Doc Cecilia.

94
00:05:51,633 --> 00:05:55,300
She said she would deliver
Dante's autopsy report later.

95
00:05:55,433 --> 00:05:56,667
Wait, wait, Bok.

96
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,433
Why are you the one
who talked to Doc Cecilia?

97
00:05:58,567 --> 00:06:00,367
It should have been me.

98
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:02,367
I ordered Dizon...

99
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:04,867
because you're losing
your focus...

100
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:07,000
when it comes to Doc Cecilia.

101
00:06:07,133 --> 00:06:08,900
You're putting
your love life first.

102
00:06:09,067 --> 00:06:13,100
Bok, that love life,
that's just trouble.

103
00:06:13,233 --> 00:06:14,733
Look at Dante.

104
00:06:14,867 --> 00:06:16,067
He put his love life first,

105
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:18,100
that's why he got killed.

106
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:27,900
Anyway, what do you think,
Conde?

107
00:06:28,033 --> 00:06:31,633
It might be better if we wait
for the autopsy report...

108
00:06:31,767 --> 00:06:33,500
before we act.

109
00:06:37,633 --> 00:06:39,633
Okay.

110
00:06:39,767 --> 00:06:43,233
For now, let's just stand by.

111
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:47,200
And report to me all the
information you get.

112
00:06:47,333 --> 00:06:49,033
Dismissed.

113
00:06:49,167 --> 00:06:51,300
Garcia, Conde...

114
00:06:51,433 --> 00:06:53,200
you guys stay.

115
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:55,300
I have something for you to do.

116
00:07:07,700 --> 00:07:12,133
Just woo her.
She's just sulking.

117
00:07:12,267 --> 00:07:13,633
- Vince?
- Where can I get...

118
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:16,400
- a birth certificate?
- Vince!

119
00:07:22,167 --> 00:07:24,400
Okay, I'll be right back.

120
00:07:26,333 --> 00:07:28,967
What's wrong with him?

121
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:30,733
Faye...

122
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:32,533
if he ignores you,

123
00:07:32,667 --> 00:07:36,233
it means he doesn't want
to talk to you.

124
00:07:36,367 --> 00:07:38,633
It's that simple, right?

125
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:46,167
What's wrong with him?

126
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:50,900
Maybe he just didn't see you.

127
00:07:51,067 --> 00:07:52,500
You think?

128
00:07:52,633 --> 00:07:54,400
Probably.

129
00:07:58,333 --> 00:07:59,933
Anyway...

130
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:12,800
Chief...

131
00:08:12,933 --> 00:08:14,933
what are you going
to ask us to do?

132
00:08:17,300 --> 00:08:19,967
Conde, what are you thinking?

133
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:22,867
Why did you stop me
from saying or discussing...

134
00:08:23,033 --> 00:08:24,300
with our colleagues

135
00:08:24,433 --> 00:08:26,333
what you suspected?

136
00:08:28,167 --> 00:08:30,600
Bok...

137
00:08:30,733 --> 00:08:35,433
did you tell anyone why we were
waiting for Dante yesterday?

138
00:08:35,567 --> 00:08:37,533
Oh, the one that
your informant said...

139
00:08:37,667 --> 00:08:41,633
that Dante's girl lives there?

140
00:08:41,767 --> 00:08:43,667
None, why?

141
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:48,767
Because I didn't put
that in the report either.

142
00:08:48,900 --> 00:08:51,500
So that means...

143
00:08:51,633 --> 00:08:54,467
only the two of us know
about it.

144
00:08:58,500 --> 00:08:59,867
Sir...

145
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:03,900
I think I know how to catch that
snake here at Station 12.

146
00:09:05,733 --> 00:09:07,900
I just hope
my suspicions are wrong.

147
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:23,100
I called you again
because I received intel.

148
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:25,667
Unfortunately...

149
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,467
Dante had a relative...

150
00:09:28,633 --> 00:09:30,700
whom he told

151
00:09:30,833 --> 00:09:31,767
before he died...

152
00:09:32,733 --> 00:09:34,800
who his true boss was.

153
00:09:40,967 --> 00:09:43,533
Here in these files...

154
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:45,833
is the address of
Dante's relative.

155
00:09:45,967 --> 00:09:48,167
Conde, tomorrow morning,

156
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:52,367
go and convince him
to cooperate with us...

157
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:56,367
so we can find out
who his boss is.

158
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:58,000
Yes, Sir.

159
00:10:15,867 --> 00:10:18,067
Okay, dismissed.

160
00:10:23,267 --> 00:10:24,967
Okay, Sir.

161
00:10:29,133 --> 00:10:31,233
For that idiot Dante.

162
00:10:35,533 --> 00:10:38,367
You're already dead, you're
still giving me a headache.

163
00:10:40,033 --> 00:10:40,767
Hello?

164
00:10:40,900 --> 00:10:42,167
Hello, Roman, we have a problem.

165
00:10:42,300 --> 00:10:43,333
Do you really miss me?

166
00:10:43,467 --> 00:10:45,533
Two calls in one day, Robles?

167
00:10:45,667 --> 00:10:46,800
<i> I'm serious.</i>

168
00:10:46,933 --> 00:10:49,700
Dante has a relative
who knows boss.

169
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:51,500
Who did you hear that from?

170
00:10:51,633 --> 00:10:53,133
Here with my colleagues

171
00:10:53,267 --> 00:10:55,067
Just keep it simple.

172
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:58,167
The mayor shouldn't be involved,
no matter what.

173
00:10:58,300 --> 00:10:59,333
Because if that happens,

174
00:10:59,467 --> 00:11:00,567
we'll all be dead.

175
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:03,000
I know, that's why I called you,
right?

176
00:11:03,133 --> 00:11:04,167
Since you already know...

177
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:05,367
well, you should know
what to do now?

178
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:07,367
Yes, I'll take care of it.

179
00:11:14,367 --> 00:11:19,100
<i>Make sure the body
of Dante Eusebio is clean.</i>

180
00:11:20,867 --> 00:11:22,400
Just follow me.

181
00:11:22,533 --> 00:11:24,667
When my techniques, for speed..

182
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:26,033
Oh...

183
00:11:38,033 --> 00:11:39,400
Why are you so slow to get up?

184
00:11:39,533 --> 00:11:40,567
Oh...

185
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,733
Because isn't it
in love stories,

186
00:11:42,900 --> 00:11:45,133
when they collide,
like this,

187
00:11:45,267 --> 00:11:46,600
slowly, in slow-motion...

188
00:11:46,733 --> 00:11:49,867
Anyway, why are you here?

189
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:53,167
I've finished Dante Eusebio's
autopsy report.

190
00:11:53,300 --> 00:11:56,167
What's up with Dante's autopsy?

191
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:59,800
Any clues that will lead
to his boss?

192
00:12:01,767 --> 00:12:04,000
No, he's clean.

193
00:12:04,133 --> 00:12:06,600
Nothing unusual.

194
00:12:06,733 --> 00:12:10,000
Is Chief there?

195
00:12:10,133 --> 00:12:12,167
Yes, he's there, upstairs.

196
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:14,833
Oh, okay, I'll go ahead.

197
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,400
Cecilia...

198
00:12:17,533 --> 00:12:18,833
Are you okay?

199
00:12:20,700 --> 00:12:22,367
Because you seem to be...

200
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:24,800
deep in thought.

201
00:12:24,933 --> 00:12:28,333
Oh, sorry, I think
I'm just tired.

202
00:12:28,467 --> 00:12:29,433
I haven't slept yet...

203
00:12:29,567 --> 00:12:31,900
to finish this autopsy.

204
00:12:32,033 --> 00:12:33,733
You haven't slept yet
in that state?

205
00:12:33,867 --> 00:12:35,833
You look so fresh.

206
00:12:38,133 --> 00:12:39,333
Okay, I'll go ahead.

207
00:12:39,467 --> 00:12:40,967
Oh, okay.

208
00:12:43,767 --> 00:12:45,500
Slow-mo, Sir?

209
00:12:45,633 --> 00:12:47,067
Sir, how's the slow-mo?

210
00:12:49,067 --> 00:12:52,233
Hey, you two, do you know what
the other slow-mo is?

211
00:12:52,367 --> 00:12:53,267
- What else, Sir?
- What else, Sir?

212
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:55,367
The one who's dying...

213
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:57,400
- Sir, you can't take a joke.
- Sir, you can't take a joke.

214
00:12:57,533 --> 00:13:02,633
You two are too invested in our
love story.

215
00:13:12,667 --> 00:13:15,833
Grandmother,
get some rest, okay?

216
00:13:15,967 --> 00:13:18,233
Okay, Bobby, thank you.

217
00:13:18,367 --> 00:13:20,400
Go to bed early, okay?

218
00:13:25,167 --> 00:13:27,267
- Good night!
- Good night.

219
00:13:46,733 --> 00:13:49,700
Oh, Bobby, you're home now?

220
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:53,767
How was captain's check-up?

221
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:57,733
The doctor said...

222
00:14:01,367 --> 00:14:03,100
maybe it's dementia.

223
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:26,267
Oh, how are your bruises?

224
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:27,600
You've been going solo,

225
00:14:27,733 --> 00:14:29,667
since you courted Miss Faye.

226
00:14:29,833 --> 00:14:30,700
That's right!

227
00:14:30,833 --> 00:14:32,267
You know, Bro,
if you were with us,

228
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:34,533
that's unlikely
to happen to you.

229
00:14:34,667 --> 00:14:38,467
Wait, what else did those who
beat you up say to you?

230
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:41,733
They said, Bro, that I should
stay away from Faye.

231
00:14:41,867 --> 00:14:44,033
That's why I have
a strong feeling...

232
00:14:44,167 --> 00:14:47,133
that Faye's family gave the
order to beat me up.

233
00:14:47,267 --> 00:14:49,167
What? Why?

234
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:50,533
Because they don't like you?

235
00:14:50,667 --> 00:14:52,533
Oh, that's impossible, Bro.

236
00:14:52,667 --> 00:14:54,567
And the mayor is very kind, Bro.

237
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:58,100
He was with us who saved
captain, remember?

238
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,800
Madam!

239
00:15:02,933 --> 00:15:07,800
Madam, I have some
hot news for you.

240
00:15:07,933 --> 00:15:12,767
From my friend who works as an
orderly at Calabari Hospital.

241
00:15:12,900 --> 00:15:14,867
Will that make my night better?

242
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:16,967
I have a feeling, Madam.

243
00:15:17,100 --> 00:15:19,900
He said Bobby and her
grandmother...

244
00:15:20,033 --> 00:15:22,000
came from the hospital earlier.

245
00:15:22,133 --> 00:15:23,400
And guess what.

246
00:15:23,533 --> 00:15:25,433
The old woman is sick...

247
00:15:27,267 --> 00:15:28,700
Dementia.

248
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:32,700
Karma is starting
to take its toll on them.

249
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:34,800
Cheers.

250
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:48,633
You know, Bobby,

251
00:15:48,767 --> 00:15:52,333
when your grandmother
and I first met,

252
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:55,033
she was looking for someone...

253
00:15:55,167 --> 00:15:57,200
to join the boxing club
in the village.

254
00:16:02,033 --> 00:16:05,667
So I was forced to join...

255
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:07,833
because...

256
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,767
I didn't want to get caught.

257
00:16:12,633 --> 00:16:15,633
But before that day,

258
00:16:15,767 --> 00:16:18,067
she told me...

259
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:20,233
not to join...

260
00:16:22,233 --> 00:16:25,833
because I punched like this.

261
00:16:33,733 --> 00:16:35,633
As for me, Bobby,

262
00:16:37,367 --> 00:16:41,667
I was being pressured to join
the league.

263
00:16:44,300 --> 00:16:50,233
They said I would be made the
center of the basketball team.

264
00:16:50,367 --> 00:16:52,533
Well,

265
00:16:52,667 --> 00:16:53,533
I couldn't refuse...

266
00:16:53,667 --> 00:16:56,033
because I was afraid
we would get caught,

267
00:16:56,167 --> 00:16:57,333
especially me.

268
00:16:57,467 --> 00:16:59,300
So...

269
00:17:00,567 --> 00:17:02,567
I joined.

270
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:04,600
Captain approached me.

271
00:17:04,733 --> 00:17:07,033
She told me, "Abdul...

272
00:17:07,167 --> 00:17:09,367
don't join.

273
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:14,100
I can feel that you're just
being forced."

274
00:17:14,233 --> 00:17:17,033
How did she know?

275
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:19,833
Because...

276
00:17:19,967 --> 00:17:21,900
this is how I shoot.

277
00:17:25,700 --> 00:17:27,233
You know,

278
00:17:29,567 --> 00:17:33,367
when mother was robbed
and killed.

279
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:38,467
I cried so hard.

280
00:17:40,567 --> 00:17:44,400
I just stopped when grandmother
came and hugged me.

281
00:17:51,433 --> 00:17:53,367
Since then,

282
00:17:53,933 --> 00:17:56,900
grandmother has been with me
in all our fights.

283
00:18:00,567 --> 00:18:04,533
That's why it hurts me to see
her like this,

284
00:18:04,667 --> 00:18:06,767
because I feel like...

285
00:18:09,367 --> 00:18:12,867
I can't be with her in this
fight that she's going through.

286
00:18:18,033 --> 00:18:20,033
I feel that...

287
00:18:21,967 --> 00:18:25,533
I can't give her courage,
especially now.

288
00:18:27,667 --> 00:18:30,400
Because even I am getting weak.

289
00:18:35,867 --> 00:18:39,267
Mar, Abdul...

290
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:40,700
I don't know what I'll do...

291
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:43,833
if something bad happens
to grandmother.

292
00:18:47,533 --> 00:18:51,733
I'm ready to trade everything
just so she can get better.

293
00:19:24,933 --> 00:19:26,633
<i> Oh! Oh!</i>

294
00:19:26,767 --> 00:19:30,733
<i>My granddaughter is beautiful.
Beautiful.</i>

295
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:33,533
<i>Do you know what's more
important to me?</i>

296
00:19:33,667 --> 00:19:34,833
<i> You.</i>

297
00:19:34,967 --> 00:19:39,000
<i>You are the most important thing
to me than anything else.</i>

298
00:19:39,133 --> 00:19:40,367
<i> I love you, Grandmother.</i>

299
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:42,133
<i> I love you.</i>

300
00:19:43,767 --> 00:19:49,100
<i>I just don't want
to leave you alone.</i>

301
00:19:49,233 --> 00:19:50,867
<i> I'll be sad.</i>

302
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:52,000
<i>Oh, what's with you,
Grandmother?</i>

303
00:19:52,133 --> 00:19:53,600
<i> That's a long way to go.</i>

304
00:19:53,733 --> 00:19:55,267
<i> You're still so strong, see?</i>

305
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:57,100
<i>We have all the time in the
world.</i>

306
00:19:57,233 --> 00:19:58,733
<i> Just remember.</i>

307
00:19:58,867 --> 00:20:00,833
<i>The grandchild
who is beautiful...</i>

308
00:20:00,967 --> 00:20:03,367
<i>- inherited grandmother's looks.
- Correct!</i>

309
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:29,533
So, Bok, Ms. Isang is sick?

310
00:20:29,667 --> 00:20:30,667
How's Bobby?

311
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:34,200
Well, she's so affected.

312
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:38,167
You know how much
she loves her grandmother.

313
00:20:38,333 --> 00:20:39,833
Don't spread the word, okay?

314
00:20:39,967 --> 00:20:41,233
I only told you.

315
00:20:41,367 --> 00:20:43,333
Of course, it's our secret.

316
00:20:43,467 --> 00:20:45,400
What do you think of me?

317
00:20:45,533 --> 00:20:49,667
But, Bok, why are we
waiting here?

318
00:20:52,267 --> 00:20:53,300
<i> What's your plan, Conde?</i>

319
00:20:55,467 --> 00:20:56,933
<i> Sir...</i>

320
00:20:57,067 --> 00:20:59,867
<i> you're going to tell us</i>

321
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:02,133
<i> that Dante said...</i>

322
00:21:02,733 --> 00:21:05,000
<i> he told a relative</i>

323
00:21:05,133 --> 00:21:08,133
<i> who his boss is.</i>

324
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:11,267
<i> Now, the syndicate...</i>

325
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:14,800
<i>will want to find out
who that relative is.</i>

326
00:21:14,933 --> 00:21:19,367
<i>Then you're going to give us
different addresses.</i>

327
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:23,100
<i>Once the syndicate goes
to that fake address,</i>

328
00:21:23,233 --> 00:21:25,100
<i> that's where we'll find out</i>

329
00:21:25,233 --> 00:21:28,167
<i>who the traitor is here
at Station 12.</i>

330
00:21:34,233 --> 00:21:37,000
That's the address
Regan was given.

331
00:21:37,133 --> 00:21:39,200
And he's the one
you're suspecting?

332
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:41,167
Oh, didn't he say earlier...

333
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:43,900
that Dante was
having a love life?

334
00:21:44,067 --> 00:21:46,300
I didn't tell anyone else.

335
00:21:46,433 --> 00:21:48,800
You said you didn't tell
anyone else, right?

336
00:21:48,933 --> 00:21:51,567
Oh, how would he know that?

337
00:21:51,700 --> 00:21:53,800
You're right.

338
00:21:53,933 --> 00:21:56,967
You know, I admire
your instincts,

339
00:21:57,100 --> 00:22:01,567
but, I hope, I hope
you're wrong this time.

340
00:22:07,700 --> 00:22:08,900
Bok...

341
00:22:09,033 --> 00:22:10,867
there's a car.

342
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:22,267
Bok, it's loaded.

343
00:22:24,100 --> 00:22:25,500
Bok...

344
00:22:25,633 --> 00:22:27,300
well, it seems
my suspicions weren't wrong.

345
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:32,400
Robles is the snake
of Station 12.

346
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:49,767
It's Robles?

347
00:22:49,933 --> 00:22:51,900
Maybe from the very beginning,
the criminals have paid him.

348
00:22:52,033 --> 00:22:53,733
But we'll only know
the answer to that...

349
00:22:53,867 --> 00:22:54,633
when we find out

350
00:22:54,767 --> 00:22:56,200
who Robles' real boss is.

351
00:22:56,333 --> 00:22:58,167
I really don't want to be nosy.

352
00:22:58,300 --> 00:23:00,033
Maybe later on,
they'll doubt me too.

353
00:23:00,167 --> 00:23:01,900
If you can't do it,

354
00:23:02,033 --> 00:23:03,367
we can easily find
a replacement.

355
00:23:03,500 --> 00:23:04,867
You know, if you could talk,

356
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:06,367
you'd think you'd be
more useful than me.

357
00:23:06,500 --> 00:23:08,733
Let's sweat it out
so we'll find out who's useless.

358
00:23:14,133 --> 00:23:15,700
You want to drop the case?

359
00:23:15,833 --> 00:23:18,467
I'd rather focus on
taking care of grandmother.

360
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:21,200
What's this nonsense, Glen?

361
00:23:21,333 --> 00:23:24,167
What's this bastard doing here?
